<Base title="Duolingo vs Babbel 2026: Which English Learning App Wins?" description="Compare Duolingo vs Babbel for English learners. Pricing, learning approach, content depth, mobile experience, and speaking practice side by side.">
 <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(articleSchema)} />
 <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(comparisonSchema)} />

 <Header platform="Duolingo vs Babbel" />

 <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-8">
    <nav aria-label="Breadcrumb" class="text-sm text-neutral-300 mb-4 flex items-center flex-wrap">
      <a href="/" class="hover:text-emerald-400">Home</a>
      <span class="mx-2">›</span>
      <a href="/compare/" class="hover:text-emerald-400">Comparisons</a>
      <span class="mx-2">›</span>
      <span class="text-neutral-400">Duolingo vs Babbel</span>
    </nav>
 <div class="mb-8">
 <span class="text-sm text-gray-400">Comparison · Updated April 2026</span>
 <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mt-2 mb-4">Duolingo vs Babbel 2026: Which English Learning App Wins?</h1>
 <a href="#verdict" class="inline-block bg-slate-800 hover:bg-gray-200 text-slate-200 text-sm font-semibold px-4 py-2 rounded-lg mt-2 md:hidden">↓ Jump to Verdict</a>
 <p class="text-lg text-gray-400">Two of the most popular English learning apps go head to head. We compare pricing, learning style, content depth, and speaking practice to help you choose.</p>
 </div>

 <!-- FTC Disclosure -->
 <div class="bg-neutral-800 border border-neutral-700 rounded-xl p-4 mb-8 text-sm text-gray-300">
 <p><strong>Disclosure:</strong> LearnEnglish.Life earns a commission when you sign up for Duolingo, Babbel, or See Guru through links on this page. This does not affect our editorial independence. <a href="/affiliate-disclosure/" class="underline">See our full affiliate disclosure</a>.</p>
 </div>

 <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-10 mb-4 text-white">Quick Verdict</h2>
 <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4 leading-relaxed">Choose <strong>Duolingo</strong> if you want to learn for free, enjoy game-like lessons, and prefer short daily sessions on your phone. Choose <strong>Babbel</strong> if you want a structured curriculum, are serious about grammar, and want lessons that teach you to hold real conversations from day one.</p>
 <p class="text-gray-300 mb-6 leading-relaxed"><strong>Our pick for most learners:</strong> Duolingo for beginners on a budget. Babbel for intermediate learners who want deeper grammar and conversation skills.</p>

 <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mb-8">
 <div class="bg-emerald-900/20 border-2 border-emerald-700 rounded-2xl p-6 text-center">
 <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-emerald-400 uppercase tracking-wide mb-2">Best for Free Learning</p>
 <p class="text-3xl font-black text-white">Duolingo</p>
 <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mt-2">Free tier available</p>
 </div>
 <div class="bg-blue-900/20 border-2 border-blue-700 rounded-2xl p-6 text-center">
 <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wide mb-2">Best for Grammar Depth</p>
 <p class="text-3xl font-black text-white">Babbel</p>
 <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mt-2">Explicit grammar teaching</p>
 </div>
 </div>

 <AdUnit slot="header" />

 <ComparisonHighlight 
 title="Duolingo vs Babbel"
 platformA={duolingo}
 platformB={babbel}
 winner="a"
 rows={comparisonRows}
 />

 <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-10 mb-4 text-white">Pricing</h2>
 <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 text-white">Duolingo</h3>
 <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4 leading-relaxed">Duolingo operates on a freemium model. The free version gives you access to the full tree of lessons, daily reviews, streaks, and most exercises. You can make real progress without spending a cent.</p>
 <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4 leading-relaxed">Duolingo Super removes ads and unlocks unlimited hearts, offline mode, and full access to all stories and listening exercises. Super costs $12.99 per month, or around $6.99 per month on an annual plan.</p>

 <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 text-white">Babbel</h3>
 <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4 leading-relaxed">Babbel does not offer a meaningful free version. You can try the first lesson of any course at no cost, but everything else requires a paid subscription. Prices range from $13.95/month to $6.95/month on an annual plan.</p>

 <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-10 mb-4 text-white">Learning Approach</h2>
 <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 text-white">Duolingo: Gamified and Addictive</h3>
 <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4 leading-relaxed">Duolingo turns learning into a game. Every lesson you complete earns you experience points. Miss a day and you lose your streak. The streak system motivates daily practice and keeps users coming back.</p>

 <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 text-white">Babbel: Structured and Practical</h3>
 <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4 leading-relaxed">Babbel takes a more traditional approach. Each lesson is built around a specific conversation scenario. Vocabulary and grammar are taught together, with clear explanations of how sentences are formed.</p>

 <BenefitCards 
 title="Why Choose These Apps?"
 benefits={benefits}
 />

 <SocialProof platform="duolingo" />
 <SocialProof platform="babbel" />

 <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-10 mb-4 text-white">Which Should You Choose?</h2>
 <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4 leading-relaxed">Choose Duolingo if you are a beginner who wants to build a daily learning habit without spending money. Choose Babbel if you are serious about understanding English grammar and want a structured curriculum.</p>

